The capitalize text style is not consistent across browsers. The jiraissue macro uses this style for the table header, which renders differently in different browsers. For instance, if the macro includes an "Author(s)" column, it will render as Author(s) in FireFox, but as "Author(S)" in Safari.

If there is a concrete specification of the capitalize style, this could end up being a bug in one of the browsers.

